  "summaryReport": "# Executive Summary\n\nThis report summarizes the technical documentation and resources shared by **tianweiliu2012** in the **#platform-guild** channel. The shared documents focus heavily on establishing the architecture for a new Slack bot, aligning with Kubernetes standards for scheduling and proposals, and utilizing structured templates for design documentation.\n\n## Highlights\n\n- **Slack Bot Framework & Datastore:** The team is building the Slack bot using the Bolt JS framework and has selected Prisma as the backing datastore.\n- **Design & Proposal Standards:** A standardized design-doc template was introduced to ensure consistency, paired with the Kubernetes Enhancements (KEP) format as a reference model.\n- **Kubernetes SIG References:** Multiple Kubernetes community resources were shared to guide job batching and runtime decisions, including the Scheduling SIG notes and SIG Node README.\n- **Onboarding & Governance:** Onboarding items have been added to the docs working-group agenda, and community governance structures were referenced to identify owners and cadences.\n",
